 stress reactions, which are placed under specific categories. The system also uses the term \"harmful use\" synonymously with substance abuse and categorizes mental disorders due to physical diseases under section F06. Furthermore, ICD-10 has abandoned the overarching term \"neurosis\" but has retained several subtypes related to the concept by renaming or reclassifying them, ensuring their continued presence in the classification system. This comprehensive and evolving framework is utilized by researchers and clinicians, such as Fink and 孟凡强 et al., for diagnosing conditions like somatoform disorders, making it an essential tool in global healthcare.", "ICD-10 MENTAL DISORDERS:ICD-10 mental disorders are discussed in the context of prevalence rates across different regions", "ICELAND:Iceland has a low suicide rate, with fewer than 5 suicides per 100,000 people, according to WHO data.", "ICU:ICU是重症监护病房的缩写，是监护室的一部分，患者在此可能因焦虑和精神异常而需要精神科会诊", "IGM:Immunoglobulin M (IgM) is an immune factor whose levels increase during stress, affecting immune function.", "IL-2:Interleukin-2 (IL-2) is an immune factor whose levels decrease during stress, affecting immune function."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}